args: Look at all these delicious baked treats!
Oh man, they smell sooo good...\nMakes me wanna take a bite!
Well, I suppose it's only right to try them\nbefore serving them to others, yes?
Don't have to tell me twice! *chomp*
Hmm... Well, they're certainly sweet\nenough—and delicious in general—\nbut they also might be a touch dry.
Hmm, yes. And if they're dry fresh out\nof the oven like this, the issue will only\nbe worse once they've cooled down.
OUTTA THE WAY, FOOLS!\nNOTTE WANTS TREATS!
Stand down, Notte! I'll not have you going\noverboard with snacks before dinner.
Cleo! Just the woman we wanted to see!\nCan you try one of these treats and let us\nknow your professional culinary opinion?
Well, I suppose one won't hurt. *munch*
Hey, no fair! What about MY professional\nculpability opinion, huh?!
Ha ha! Very well, Notte. Open wide.
They're quite good, but I believe you need\nto heat the oven longer before putting\nthem in.

If an oven is not sufficiently preheated,
your dough will slacken, and it will also
take more time to cook, causing them to
dry out.
See, I knew you'd be able to help, Cleo!\nRight then. It's on to batch number two.\nThese are going to knock your socks off!

Well, I have a number of chores to attend
to, so I will check in on you in a while.
Oh, and dinner is still on the way, so do
try not to make TOO many sweets, yes?
...If this is your idea of ＂not making\ntoo many,＂ I shudder to think of your\nidea of ＂a lot.＂
Er, sorry. We sort of got...carried away.

＂We have too many treats＂ is a SUPER 
weird complaint for something this delish!
Seriously, Cleo, your tip about the oven
was right on point.
I tell you what—these puppies look so\ngood, I could horf 'em all down right now.
Please do not ＂horf them all down,＂\nor I fear you will not be able to\neat your dinner for a week.

That being said, these aren't the type of
thing that will keep well, so we'd best
decide what to do with them in the
very near future.
I take full responsibility, and will consume\nevery last one to ensure none are wasted.
You can't eat all those—you'd explode!\nThere's enough here for like fifty Nottes!
And speeeeeeaking of Notte, she's more\nthan happy to help with treat disposal.
No. This is my fault, and I can't impose\non anyone else to fix it.
These treats were a group effort; there is\nno need for you to take full responsibility.

Also, your plan is simply untenable.
You cannot eat this many treats in one
sitting—I don't even think Ranzal is
capable of such a feat.
In that case, what say we hand 'em out to\nHalidom folks and the nearby village?
That's a great idea—even a mountain\nof treats like this is no match for that\nmany hungry mouths.
Then let us divide them up and begin\nthe deliveries at once. Treats such as\nthese are better when fresh, after all.
Aw, it ain't no big thing. Friends gotta\ncome together to help each other when\nthe chips are down, after all!
In that case, I'll do my best to make\nsure these snacks find their way\nto all those happy stomachs!
...Well, we've certainly cut down\non the number of surplus treats.
And while the residents of the Halidom\nwere certainly glad to receive them,\nI wonder how things will go here.
I wouldn't worry. There are a number of\nchildren in this village, and I've never\nknown a youngster to refuse a treat.
Whoa, something smells goooood!\nWhere'd you guys come from?
We have come from the Halidom in the\nMistholt to deliver treats to all of you.
Yes, and they're all homemade.\nPlease take as many as you like!
Hoy, what's the meaning of this?!
Who said you could talk to my boy?!
I assure you, sir, we meant no harm.\nWe were merely—
Causin' trouble is what you were doing!\nWe've no need of you Mistholt types here,\nso get lost and forget the way back!
Dammit, boy! How many times have I told\nyou not to take things from strangers?!
Well, he was a rather wary fellow.
Do we truly look so suspicious?
Um, sorry about my father, ma'am.
It's only natural for a parent to teach a\nchild not to accept things from strangers.
In that case, we'll just have to ensure\nthat we are NOT strangers.
Greetings! My name is Sharena!\nAnd what is your name, young man?
Mathias, is it? Well then, it seems we're\nproper acquaintances now—or perhaps\neven friends!
And what could be wrong with giving\ntreats to a friend, mmm?
Goodness, but this is all\nbeing laid on a bit thick...
What's wrong, Cleo? This is a perfect\nplan, is it not?
Yeah! You're my friend now, which means\nmy father can't be upset with me!

While you are observing the letter of the
law, you trample the spirit of it in the dust.
There is no way this boy's father will ever
fall for such a ham-handed runaround.
Then if he gets angry at Mathias,\nI will bear that anger alongside him.\nFor that is what true friends do!

*siiigh* Well, as there is CLEARLY no
talking you out of this, I suppose I should
go along. Three can bear the brunt of
anger better than two, after all.
Exactly! Now then, Mathias, reach your\nhands in there and take all the treats\nyou can handle.
Oh yeah! They're as good as Mom's!
Really?! Oh, but I'm so delighted!\nThank you for saying so.
(This little escapade is all well and good,\nbut I can't help wondering why Mathias's\nfather was so upset with our being here.)
Eeek! Careful, now! If you jump at me,\nthe treats will end up on the ground!
